00:56:03,680 --> 00:56:06,717
- I'm not going to play with him.
- Gupta, relax, would you?

739
00:56:06,800 --> 00:56:09,678
- He isn't a spy.
- How do you know?

740
00:56:09,760 --> 00:56:14,231
He could be recording
everything we say. A wire in his shirt.

741
00:56:14,320 --> 00:56:16,550
A microphone up in his ass.

742
00:56:17,960 --> 00:56:22,476
- I'm not going to lose my job.
- Fine.

743
00:56:22,560 --> 00:56:25,154
- What if we x-rayed him?
- Yes.

744
00:56:26,960 --> 00:56:28,871
Close your eyes.

745
00:56:38,680 --> 00:56:42,150
- OK. So you are clean.
- Good. Let's play cards.

746
00:56:42,240 --> 00:56:45,676
I will have money.
But... Friday.

747
00:56:45,760 --> 00:56:49,514
Don't worry about it. We play for
unclaimed items from the Lost and Found.

748
00:56:49,600 --> 00:56:52,910
You'll be amazed
at what people leave at airports. Come.

749
00:56:53,000 --> 00:56:56,197
[Viktor] I have two nines and two nines.

750
00:56:56,280 --> 00:56:58,191
[Viktor] Four nines. Thank you.

751
00:56:59,480 --> 00:57:02,597
- [Enrique] Careful.
- [Mulroy] Watch out.

752
00:57:02,680 --> 00:57:07,549
- [Enrique] We have a question for you.
- [Mulroy] Yeah, we're just curious.

753
00:57:07,640 --> 00:57:09,437
[Gupta] What is in the can?

754
00:57:09,520 --> 00:57:11,988
- [Viktor] This?
- [Mulroy] We saw the x-ray.

755
00:57:12,080 --> 00:57:14,150
[Gupta]
We know there's no nuts in there.

756
00:57:15,080 --> 00:57:16,991
[Viktor] What is in there?

757
00:57:17,120 --> 00:57:19,031
This is jazz.

758
00:57:19,840 --> 00:57:21,558
- Jazz?
- Jazz, yes.

759
00:57:21,640 --> 00:57:24,029
- Jazz?
- Yes.

760
00:57:24,120 --> 00:57:25,633
[All laugh]

761
00:57:25,720 --> 00:57:29,235
You sure it's jazz in there?
It might be the blues.

762
00:57:29,320 --> 00:57:31,595
- Or salsa.
- Maybe it's Stevie Wonder.

763
00:57:31,680 --> 00:57:34,353
- No, no, is jazz.
- OK, guys. OK.

764
00:57:34,440 --> 00:57:36,749
For tonight's grand prize, we have...

765
00:57:38,720 --> 00:57:40,472
Show them, Gupta.

766
00:57:40,560 --> 00:57:42,391
I found this upstairs.

767
00:57:42,480 --> 00:57:45,040
Virgin Air, first class lounge.

768
00:57:45,120 --> 00:57:47,031
There you go.

769
00:57:47,760 --> 00:57:49,432
And... they belong to?

770
00:57:49,520 --> 00:57:51,112
Cher.

771
00:57:51,200 --> 00:57:52,713
Cher?

772
00:57:52,800 --> 00:57:54,233
As in... Cher?

773
00:57:54,320 --> 00:57:55,514
Yeah. Cher.

774
00:57:55,600 --> 00:57:57,795
I checked it out.
There were witnesses.

775
00:57:57,880 --> 00:58:00,110
Those are Cher's panties.

776
00:58:00,200 --> 00:58:01,838
- Ready?
- Hurry up.

777
00:58:01,920 --> 00:58:04,434
So, will we share the panties?

778
00:58:04,520 --> 00:58:05,919
- No, no, no.
- Not if I win.

779
00:58:06,000 --> 00:58:07,513
- Come on.
- Wait a second.

780
00:58:08,800 --> 00:58:12,839
<i>[Tannoy] United Airlines
flight number 801 to Narita</i>

781
00:58:12,920 --> 00:58:14,990
<i>is now announcing final boarding.</i>

782
00:58:15,080 --> 00:58:18,436
[Viktor] "You can't.
That is mine."

783
00:58:20,440 --> 00:58:22,954
"You can get so confused."

784
00:58:23,040 --> 00:58:24,473
[Amelia] Viktor?

785
00:58:24,560 --> 00:58:25,834
[Amelia] Well, hi.

786
00:58:27,000 --> 00:58:28,035
[Viktor] Please.

787
00:58:28,120 --> 00:58:30,111
- [Amelia] How are you?
- [Viktor] Good.

788
00:58:30,200 --> 00:58:31,952
[Amelia] Man.

789
00:58:32,040 --> 00:58:36,636
I am so sorry about what happened
last time, asking you out like that.

790
00:58:36,720 --> 00:58:39,518
I'm so used to guys
trying to grab my ass at 30,000 feet

791
00:58:39,600 --> 00:58:43,718
that when I meet somebody that doesn't,
I don't know how to react.

792
00:58:43,800 --> 00:58:45,950
- Let's just start over.
- Yes, OK.

793
00:58:46,040 --> 00:58:48,554
- Are you coming or going?
- I don't know. Both.

794
00:58:48,640 --> 00:58:50,551
Tell me about it.

795
00:58:51,000 --> 00:58:52,194
Napoleon?

796
00:58:52,280 --> 00:58:58,037
Yeah. I read a lot of history books.
They're long and cheap.

797
00:58:58,120 --> 00:59:01,078
Like 1200 pages for $9.99.
You can't beat that.

798
00:59:01,160 --> 00:59:04,630
- But Napoleon?
- Yeah. He's one of my favorites.

799
00:59:05,640 --> 00:59:07,995
- You know what saved Napoleon's life?
- No.

800
00:59:08,080 --> 00:59:09,399
- His ego.
- Ego?

801
00:59:09,480 --> 00:59:10,469
Yes.

802
00:59:10,560 --> 00:59:12,790
After he loses the Battle of Waterloo,

803
00:59:12,880 --> 00:59:16,839
Napoleon isolates himself
on the tiny island of Saint Helena.

804
00:59:16,920 --> 00:59:19,354
No one knows exactly
what happens next,

805
00:59:19,440 --> 00:59:21,670
but the version I like goes like this:

806
00:59:22,640 --> 00:59:25,996
He's very depressed
and decides to take his own life.

807
00:59:26,640 --> 00:59:30,599
But Napoleon believes himself
to be of such superhuman strength

808
00:59:30,680 --> 00:59:34,434
that he takes six times the amount
of poison needed to do the job.

809
00:59:34,520 --> 00:59:38,911
His stomach is so full up with poison
that his body rejects it,

810
00:59:39,000 --> 00:59:40,831
and he doesn't die.

811
00:59:40,920 --> 00:59:44,071
See? Ego. Saved his life.

812
00:59:44,160 --> 00:59:46,310
Maybe he need glasses.

813
00:59:46,400 --> 00:59:49,073
- Glasses?
- Yes. To read words on bottle.

814
00:59:49,160 --> 00:59:51,071
Poison.

815
00:59:52,680 --> 00:59:55,069
It's funny you should say that.

816
00:59:55,160 --> 00:59:57,754
Rumor has it
that Napoleon was farsighted.

817
00:59:57,840 --> 00:59:59,432
- There you go.
- There you go.

818
00:59:59,520 --> 01:00:02,159
- There you go.
- And there you go.

819
01:00:02,240 --> 01:00:05,038
I think we're rewriting history
right here.

820
01:00:05,120 --> 01:00:07,076
Why don't we talk about it over lunch?

821
01:00:08,120 --> 01:00:10,998
Oh, my God, I can't believe it.
I just asked you out again.

822
01:00:11,120 --> 01:00:12,997
I just did it again.

823
01:00:13,080 --> 01:00:14,718
[Amelia laughs]

824
01:00:14,800 --> 01:00:17,189
I'm so...
Just stay away from me, Viktor, OK?

825
01:00:17,280 --> 01:00:20,909
I'm sick. I don't have the ability
to be alone for five seconds.

826
01:00:21,000 --> 01:00:21,989
OK.

827
01:00:23,120 --> 01:00:25,554
- OK, what?
- OK.

828
01:00:25,640 --> 01:00:27,631
Lunch... with you.

829
01:00:29,080 --> 01:00:30,877
- You'll have lunch with me?
- Yes.

830
01:00:30,960 --> 01:00:33,520
You're not running for a flight or?

831
01:00:33,600 --> 01:00:34,919
I wait.

832
01:00:35,000 --> 01:00:36,911
<i>[Pager beeps]</i>

833
01:00:38,680 --> 01:00:40,636
- It's me.
- You. Yes.

834
01:00:40,720 --> 01:00:43,075
I'm sorry.
I just got paged.

835
01:00:43,160 --> 01:00:45,720
You work?

836
01:00:45,800 --> 01:00:47,518
- No.
- Ah.

837
01:00:47,600 --> 01:00:50,319
Three of you. Crowded.

838
01:00:50,400 --> 01:00:52,595
Stay away from me, Viktor.

839
01:00:53,680 --> 01:00:57,355
I'm... I have a serious problem.
I'm as bad as Napoleon.

840
01:00:57,440 --> 01:01:01,592
I just keep ingesting these poisonous
men until I make myself sick.

841
01:01:01,680 --> 01:01:04,399
- You're not sick, Amelia. No.
- No?

842
01:01:04,480 --> 01:01:07,677
No. You're a little... farsighted.

843
01:01:10,840 --> 01:01:13,559
- I have to go.
- I have to stay.

844
01:01:13,640 --> 01:01:16,712
- Story of my life.
- Me, too.

845
01:01:32,280 --> 01:01:34,794
[Thurman]
Your CBP inspection's in three days.

846
01:01:34,880 --> 01:01:37,713
The FBI and Homeland Security
will tour the airport,

847
01:01:37,800 --> 01:01:42,590
spend two hours observing these offices
before your interview process begins.

848
01:01:43,320 --> 01:01:45,231
How much does Navorski make?

849
01:01:46,440 --> 01:01:47,714
Sir?

850
01:01:47,800 --> 01:01:50,394
How much does he make?
How much are they paying him?

851
01:01:51,680 --> 01:01:54,274
They're paying him cash under the table.

852
01:01:54,360 --> 01:01:56,510
I know that. How much?

853
01:01:57,560 --> 01:01:59,516
$19 an hour.

854
01:01:59,600 --> 01:02:03,559
Unbelievable.
Do you know that's more than I make?

855
01:02:03,640 --> 01:02:05,676
That's New York City construction.

856
01:02:06,760 --> 01:02:09,320
One of my own men
came up to me the other day.

857
01:02:09,400 --> 01:02:12,039
Asked me
if I wanted to join the big pool.

858
01:02:12,120 --> 01:02:13,519
Look at him.

859
01:02:13,600 --> 01:02:16,831
Place a bet on when Navorski's
going to leave this airport.

860
01:02:16,920 --> 01:02:18,797
Have you heard about this?

861
01:02:20,640 --> 01:02:22,517
I have January 3rd.

862
01:02:26,640 --> 01:02:28,551
Bring him in.

863
01:02:28,640 --> 01:02:32,189
Jake, he has no nationality.
OK? No country.

864
01:02:32,280 --> 01:02:36,990
He's a national security risk, according
to my interpretation of Section 2.12.

865
01:02:37,080 --> 01:02:40,868
I want you to put him in a detention
centre and run a clearance on him.

866
01:02:40,960 --> 01:02:42,871
That's all I want.

867
01:02:44,440 --> 01:02:46,351
What about a federal prison?

868
01:02:47,600 --> 01:02:50,353
What about another airport?

869
01:02:50,440 --> 01:02:52,795
Hello? Hello?

870
01:02:56,240 --> 01:02:59,437
We're detaining so many people,
there's no room anywhere.

871
01:03:00,160 --> 01:03:04,312
- Did you try the FBI?
- I tried everybody. Nobody'll take him.

872
01:03:04,400 --> 01:03:06,789
You want me to bring him back
to the terminal?

873
01:03:06,880 --> 01:03:10,270
No. From now on, Navorski lives here.

874
01:03:19,200 --> 01:03:25,309
The people who are coming here today
will be observing me, inspecting me.

875
01:03:26,160 --> 01:03:29,789
But most of all they will be looking
at the way that this airport is run.

876
01:03:29,880 --> 01:03:34,829
So let's show them why this is the
number-one airport in the United States.

877
01:03:34,920 --> 01:03:38,276
[Frank]
We process about 600 planes a day,

878
01:03:38,360 --> 01:03:40,874
with a processing time
of 37 minutes per plane,

879
01:03:40,960 --> 01:03:42,871
about 60 seconds per passenger...

880
01:03:42,960 --> 01:03:45,394
...to be brought into the country.

881
01:03:45,480 --> 01:03:48,756
We keep it as clean as possible.

882
01:03:48,840 --> 01:03:51,035
- What do you import?
- Computer software.

883
01:03:51,120 --> 01:03:52,553
That's a lot of walnuts.

884
01:03:52,640 --> 01:03:55,632
Yeah.
My mother-in-law loves these things.

885
01:03:55,720 --> 01:03:58,280
Every time I go to Brazil,
I bring her back a bag.

886
01:03:58,360 --> 01:04:00,999
- Your mother-in-law?
- Yeah.

887
01:04:01,080 --> 01:04:02,991
Mind if I try one?

888
01:04:12,120 --> 01:04:14,998
How did you know
those weren't for his mother-in-law?

889
01:04:15,080 --> 01:04:16,877
If he's married,
where's his ring?

890
01:04:16,960 --> 01:04:20,157
And if he's divorced,
who still talks to their mother-in-law?

891
01:04:20,240 --> 01:04:24,313
I'm sorry, but really.
No offence to mother-in-laws, but...

892
01:04:24,400 --> 01:04:26,152
- Sir.
- Yeah.

893
01:04:27,520 --> 01:04:29,875
Sir, we have a situation upstairs.

894
01:04:29,960 --> 01:04:32,315
- It'll have to wait.
- No. This won't wait.

895
01:04:32,400 --> 01:04:36,757
When the 9.12 from Toronto landed, they
found four prescriptions without an MPL.

896
01:04:36,840 --> 01:04:39,354
They tried to take the pills away
and he went nuts.

897
01:04:39,440 --> 01:04:42,000
There he is.
We think they're for his father.

898
01:04:42,080 --> 01:04:44,799
Sir, sir, calm down.
Put your weapons down.

899
01:04:44,880 --> 01:04:48,759
Everybody keep your weapons...
All right. We're here to help you.

900
01:04:48,840 --> 01:04:51,877
We're here to help you, sir.
All right. Give me the knife.

901
01:04:51,960 --> 01:04:53,552
- Where's he from?
- Russia.

902
01:04:53,640 --> 01:04:56,154
The only interpreter
we got is in Newark.

903
01:04:56,240 --> 01:04:59,789
- We have to get someone to talk to him.
- I have an idea, sir.

904
01:05:03,280 --> 01:05:05,191
Viktor.

905
01:05:05,880 --> 01:05:07,836
- Viktor.
- [Viktor speaks Bulgarian]

906
01:05:07,920 --> 01:05:10,354
Oh...

907
01:05:10,440 --> 01:05:12,351
I need your help.

908
01:05:13,480 --> 01:05:16,278
His name is Milodragovich.
He lives near you.

909
01:05:16,360 --> 01:05:18,032
He may not speak your dialect,

910
01:05:18,120 --> 01:05:20,395
but I need you to translate
and help me out.

911
01:05:20,480 --> 01:05:23,233
- I help you? Why?
- I don't want anybody to get hurt.

912
01:05:23,320 --> 01:05:24,639
This guy's very upset.

913
01:05:24,720 --> 01:05:27,757
Just calm him down
and I'll let you back in the terminal.

914
01:05:27,840 --> 01:05:31,230
No. New York.
No red stamp. Green. I green.

915
01:05:31,400 --> 01:05:32,469
- New York.
- OK, yes.

916
01:05:32,560 --> 01:05:34,437
- You say yes?
- Yes.

917
01:05:34,520 --> 01:05:37,034
- OK. OK, OK, OK.
- Stay out!

918
01:05:37,120 --> 01:05:41,079
We have somebody here to talk to you.
Somebody to talk to you. Go ahead.

919
01:05:41,240 --> 01:05:43,390
Stay out!

920
01:05:43,480 --> 01:05:45,391
[Speaks Bulgarian]

921
01:05:50,000 --> 01:05:51,911
[Speaks Russian]

922
01:05:59,120 --> 01:06:00,394
So?

923
01:06:01,000 --> 01:06:05,790
OK, tell him in order to export
medicines from this country,

924
01:06:05,880 --> 01:06:12,069
he needs to have the proper form,
a Medicinal Purchase License.

925
01:06:12,160 --> 01:06:14,037
OK? You understand me, Viktor?

926
01:06:14,120 --> 01:06:16,031
[Speaks Bulgarian]

927
01:06:34,920 --> 01:06:39,710
He say he bring
the medicine for his father.

928
01:06:44,920 --> 01:06:49,038
This why he go to Canada.
Medicine for father.

929
01:06:49,120 --> 01:06:50,348
It doesn't matter.

930
01:06:50,440 --> 01:06:55,195
His plane landed in the US.
He needs to have the right form.

931
01:06:55,280 --> 01:06:57,191
[Speaks Bulgarian]

932
01:07:06,600 --> 01:07:08,830
He did not know
he need this document.

933
01:07:08,920 --> 01:07:10,990
No one say to him
he need document form.

934
01:07:11,080 --> 01:07:12,308
I'm saying it to him.

935
01:07:12,400 --> 01:07:17,633
He needs to have the form signed by
the hospital who is treating his father.

936
01:07:17,720 --> 01:07:20,678
These medicines
have to stay in the United States.

937
01:07:20,760 --> 01:07:22,034
They have to stay here.

938
01:07:22,120 --> 01:07:24,031
[Speaks Bulgarian]

939
01:07:38,760 --> 01:07:41,672
He... He's begging you.

940
01:07:41,760 --> 01:07:44,069
I know. I can see that he's begging.

941
01:07:48,160 --> 01:07:49,559
I'm sorry, sir.

942
01:07:50,720 --> 01:07:55,589
You'll have to take a flight in the
morning. The medicine stays here.

943
01:07:56,720 --> 01:07:58,631
I'm sorry.

944
01:07:59,280 --> 01:08:01,475
[Speaks Bulgarian]

945
01:08:02,000 --> 01:08:03,797
[Woman] Send him down!

946
01:08:05,440 --> 01:08:07,795
[Milodragovich sobs]

947
01:08:08,960 --> 01:08:11,679
Thank you, Viktor.
Good job. Let's go.

948
01:08:16,800 --> 01:08:18,711
Whoa.

949
01:08:19,400 --> 01:08:20,958
Goat.

950
01:08:21,040 --> 01:08:25,670
- What?
- Goat. It medicine is for goat.

951
01:08:26,400 --> 01:08:31,428
- Goat?
- Yes. Medicine is for goat. Goat.

952
01:08:31,520 --> 01:08:33,078
[Whimpers]

953
01:08:33,160 --> 01:08:35,390
- He said that?
- Yes.

954
01:08:35,480 --> 01:08:37,357
He say...

955
01:08:37,440 --> 01:08:41,228
We not understand.
I not understand "goat".

956
01:08:42,320 --> 01:08:44,959
Why? What are you saying?
You misunderstood him?

957
01:08:45,040 --> 01:08:48,191
- It's not for his dying father?
- No. No.

958
01:08:48,280 --> 01:08:53,752
The... Krakozhia...
The name for "father"...

959
01:08:53,840 --> 01:08:56,149
sound like "goat".

960
01:08:56,240 --> 01:08:58,151
I make mistake.

961
01:08:58,240 --> 01:09:00,151
[Chuckles]

962
01:09:06,160 --> 01:09:08,037
Why are you doing this, Viktor?

963
01:09:08,120 --> 01:09:11,237
Medicine is for... goat.

964
01:09:11,960 --> 01:09:13,473
- No, it's not.
- Yes.

965
01:09:13,560 --> 01:09:15,391
- No.
- Yes.

966
01:09:15,480 --> 01:09:17,550
You read the blue immigration form.

967
01:09:17,640 --> 01:09:18,629
- Blue?
- Yes. Blue.

968
01:09:18,720 --> 01:09:20,551
- Blue?
- Blue. The blue form.

969
01:09:20,640 --> 01:09:24,155
The one that says if it's an animal,
he doesn't need the license.

970
01:09:24,240 --> 01:09:28,233
Then he can bring the drugs in.
That's good, Viktor. That's very good.

971
01:09:30,040 --> 01:09:32,508
Why are you doing this? Huh?

972
01:09:32,600 --> 01:09:35,433
You don't know him.
You don't know the rules.

973
01:09:35,520 --> 01:09:37,795
Look at me.

974
01:09:37,880 --> 01:09:39,791
I was going to help you.

975
01:09:41,400 --> 01:09:45,234
Now I want you to ask him...
No, not you.

976
01:09:45,320 --> 01:09:48,118
I want you to ask him.
I want to hear him say it.

977
01:09:48,200 --> 01:09:52,034
I want to hear him say
who the medicine is for.

978
01:09:52,120 --> 01:09:54,998
Please. Who the medicine is for.

979
01:09:57,920 --> 01:09:59,831
[Speaks Bulgarian]

980
