You got to do this for me.

1197
01:27:33,280 --> 01:27:36,556
You'll get really fat
with all the food I'm going to give you.

1198
01:27:36,640 --> 01:27:41,031
But, please, do this for me. It will be
the last thing I ask you to do.

1199
01:27:58,960 --> 01:28:02,748
He waits for you to answer at Sbarro.

1200
01:28:06,840 --> 01:28:11,675
- I have to work.
- He will wait.

1201
01:28:50,960 --> 01:28:52,871
[Cheering]

1202
01:29:01,160 --> 01:29:03,071
[Viktor chuckles]

1203
01:29:13,080 --> 01:29:14,991
- How was your flight?
- Good.

1204
01:29:16,280 --> 01:29:18,157
Thanks.

1205
01:29:21,960 --> 01:29:25,509
- Is something wrong?
- You'll have to come with us.

1206
01:29:25,600 --> 01:29:28,831
You're kidding.
I come through here twice a month.

1207
01:29:28,920 --> 01:29:30,797
Please follow me.

1208
01:29:30,880 --> 01:29:32,791
I'm supposed to be meeting somebody.

1209
01:29:55,120 --> 01:29:58,271
<i>[Frank] In my line of work,
there are three things that matter.</i>

1210
01:29:58,360 --> 01:30:03,150
The person, the document and the story.

1211
01:30:04,920 --> 01:30:08,913
Find the truth of one
and you find the truth of all three.

1212
01:30:09,000 --> 01:30:11,275
I need your help finding the truth.

1213
01:30:13,040 --> 01:30:16,077
Do you know a man
named Viktor Navorski?

1214
01:30:16,160 --> 01:30:17,673
Yes.

1215
01:30:18,320 --> 01:30:21,232
Do you know why he's here
and where he's from?

1216
01:30:21,320 --> 01:30:23,993
No. We're just friends.

1217
01:30:24,080 --> 01:30:29,950
Have you noticed that he hides a can
of Dry Roasted Peanuts in his bag?

1218
01:30:30,040 --> 01:30:31,314
