to the Ramada Inn on Lexington.

1223
01:30:43,080 --> 01:30:45,196
Has he told you why he's in New York?

1224
01:30:45,280 --> 01:30:46,508
No.

1225
01:30:46,600 --> 01:30:50,309
- Has he told you where he lives?
- No. We just met at the airport.

1226
01:30:50,400 --> 01:30:54,109
All I know is that he's a building
contractor, living out of a suitcase.

1227
01:30:54,200 --> 01:30:55,474
That's it.

1228
01:30:55,560 --> 01:30:57,915
- He's a contractor?
- Yeah.

1229
01:30:58,000 --> 01:30:59,911
That's what he said?

1230
01:31:02,840 --> 01:31:06,594
Amelia. I'm just curious.

1231
01:31:06,680 --> 01:31:10,639
You are the kind of woman
who can get any guy she wants.

1232
01:31:13,240 --> 01:31:15,356
Why Viktor Navorski?

1233
01:31:17,280 --> 01:31:21,592
That's something a guy like you
could never understand.

1234
01:31:43,920 --> 01:31:48,436
I guess you missed your flight again.
Or maybe you have a bad travel agent.

1235
01:31:48,520 --> 01:31:50,636
Please. Sit.

1236
01:31:50,720 --> 01:31:53,598
It's OK, Viktor. All men lie.

1237
01:31:53,680 --> 01:31:57,116
- At least you're not very good at it.
- I did not lie.

1238
01:31:57,200 --> 01:32:00,749
You told me you were delayed.
You never said it was for nine months.

1239
01:32:01,760 --> 01:32:04,832
Maybe you see the man
the way you want see the man.

1240
01:32:04,920 --> 01:32:08,993
So what am I seeing?
Who are you?

1241
01:32:09,520 --> 01:32:11,829
- I...
- Unacceptable?

1242
01:32:11,920 --> 01:32:14,070
Yes. Yes.

1243
01:32:14,160 --> 01:32:16,071
You want to hear the funny part?

1244
01:32:16,800 --> 01:32:18,472
I broke up with him.

1245
01:32:18,560 --> 01:32:21,028
I was coming here to tell you
he's out of my life.

1246
01:32:21,120 --> 01:32:24,908
I'm free. I got tired of waiting.

1247
01:32:25,000 --> 01:32:26,911
At least we have that in common.

1248
01:32:31,440 --> 01:32:37,117
Amelia, you know what Napoleon
give to Josephine when he win Bavaria?

1249
01:32:38,800 --> 01:32:40,313
No.

1250
01:32:40,400 --> 01:32:42,391
I show you.

1251
01:32:42,480 --> 01:32:44,391
[Footsteps]

1252
01:32:46,720 --> 01:32:48,631
Please. Please.

1253
01:32:52,400 --> 01:32:54,311
Sit. Please.

1254
01:33:05,360 --> 01:33:09,876
That was gift.
Napoleon to Josephine.

1255
01:33:09,960 --> 01:33:12,428
One thousand fountains.

1256
01:33:14,120 --> 01:33:15,633
You built this for me?

1257
01:33:15,720 --> 01:33:20,396
Please. Sit. Don't get wet.

1258
01:33:21,480 --> 01:33:23,391
[Viktor strains]

1259
01:33:29,760 --> 01:33:31,671
[Viktor] Come on.

1260
01:33:32,760 --> 01:33:35,035
Oh... [speaks Bulgarian]

1261
01:33:35,120 --> 01:33:36,189
It no work.

1262
01:33:36,280 --> 01:33:41,035
It should shoot,
big water up to ceiling.

1263
01:33:42,400 --> 01:33:47,235
Just tell me the truth.
Did you escape from an institution?

1264
01:33:51,000 --> 01:33:52,911
[Amelia] Are you a criminal?

1265
01:33:55,880 --> 01:33:57,552
You're living here, Viktor.

1266
01:33:57,640 --> 01:34:01,519
You're living at Gate 67.
I just want to know why.

1267
01:34:01,600 --> 01:34:03,511
Here. I show you.

1268
01:34:14,840 --> 01:34:16,193
My father.

1269
01:34:16,280 --> 01:34:19,477
Viktor, please tell me
your father isn't in that peanut can.

1270
01:34:26,600 --> 01:34:28,511
This is jazz.

1271
01:34:34,720 --> 01:34:37,439
My father, Dimitar Asenov Navorski,

1272
01:34:37,520 --> 01:34:42,196
see this photograph
in Hungarian newspaper 1958.

1273
01:34:43,360 --> 01:34:45,954
He say he look at photograph
for seven days.

1274
01:34:46,040 --> 01:34:47,951
Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday...

1275
01:34:48,440 --> 01:34:50,351
Who are they?

1276
01:34:50,520 --> 01:34:53,956
Count Basie, Dizzy Gillespie,
Thelonious Monk, Sonny Rollins,

1277
01:34:54,040 --> 01:34:55,951
Art Blakey, Max Kaminsky.

1278
01:34:56,040 --> 01:34:58,395
57 of them all together.

1279
01:34:58,480 --> 01:35:02,837
After looking at photograph
for seven days, my father has idea.

1280
01:35:02,920 --> 01:35:07,755
He begin to write letters to club,
Lickety Split, Snookie's Sugar Bowl.

1281
01:35:07,840 --> 01:35:12,914
He ask the nuns to write English.
Hundreds letters.

1282
01:35:13,000 --> 01:35:14,911
And then he wait.

1283
01:35:15,800 --> 01:35:19,475
He wait month, week, year.

1284
01:35:19,560 --> 01:35:22,472
My father wait 40 year.

1285
01:35:26,800 --> 01:35:29,030
And they all sign names.

1286
01:35:32,000 --> 01:35:33,991
One by one.

1287
01:35:49,040 --> 01:35:53,511
They all write their name
and send it to my father.

1288
01:35:59,720 --> 01:36:01,631
All but not one.

1289
01:36:03,520 --> 01:36:05,238
Benny Golson.

1290
01:36:08,680 --> 01:36:10,591
Saxophone.

1291
01:36:10,680 --> 01:36:15,754
My father die before Benny Golson
write his name and send to my father.

1292
01:36:15,840 --> 01:36:19,549
So I make him promise.
I keep promise.

1293
01:36:23,280 --> 01:36:28,559
I promise I will go New York,
find Benny Golson,

1294
01:36:28,640 --> 01:36:31,438
have him write name to put in can.

1295
01:36:32,280 --> 01:36:35,955
And you've been living here
so you could do this for your father?

1296
01:36:36,640 --> 01:36:38,551
Maybe I think he do it for me.

1297
01:36:44,400 --> 01:36:48,075
You say you are waiting for something.

1298
01:36:49,400 --> 01:36:53,109
And I say to you,
"Yes, yes. We all wait".

1299
01:36:56,480 --> 01:36:58,391
What are you waiting for?

1300
01:37:00,400 --> 01:37:04,439
You. I wait for you.

1301
01:37:59,160 --> 01:38:00,434
What?

1302
01:38:04,800 --> 01:38:06,870
The war is over.

1303
01:38:06,960 --> 01:38:10,509
<i>... the right-wing military coup
that ousted President Vagobagin...</i>

1304
01:38:10,600 --> 01:38:13,797
[all sing the Krakozhian
National Anthem in Bulgarian]

1305
01:38:35,920 --> 01:38:38,957
All right, everybody.
Let's raise your glasses.

1306
01:38:39,040 --> 01:38:42,794
Let's have a toast to my friend,
Viktor "The Goat".

1307
01:38:42,880 --> 01:38:44,791
- [Bleats]
- [All bleat]

1308
01:38:44,880 --> 01:38:46,950
May he never lose his country again.

1309
01:38:47,640 --> 01:38:49,073
Krakozhia!

1310
01:38:49,160 --> 01:38:52,914
Amelia! You here early!

1311
01:38:53,000 --> 01:38:55,150
Hello. Amelia, look.

1312
01:38:55,240 --> 01:38:57,754
Peace, peace in the war.
The war, peace. Come.

1313
01:38:57,840 --> 01:39:00,638
See, the war,
the war Krakozhia is over.

1314
01:39:00,720 --> 01:39:03,314
Peace. The war is over.

1315
01:39:07,000 --> 01:39:10,151
- You know my friend in Washington.
- Yes, yes.

1316
01:39:10,240 --> 01:39:12,913
He has a lot of connections. Here.

1317
01:39:13,000 --> 01:39:14,638
It's a pass, Viktor.

1318
01:39:14,720 --> 01:39:17,473
A one-day travel emergency visa
with your name on it.

1319
01:39:17,560 --> 01:39:19,232
- Wha... Visa?
- Yes.

1320
01:39:19,320 --> 01:39:21,390
- From your friend?
- Yeah.

1321
01:39:21,480 --> 01:39:25,314
Just go to New York, find that last name
and put it in the can.

1322
01:39:26,080 --> 01:39:27,149
- I go New York?
- Yes.

1323
01:39:27,240 --> 01:39:28,719
I go New York!

1324
01:39:28,800 --> 01:39:30,677
[All cheer]

1325
01:39:36,520 --> 01:39:39,910
Amelia, you come with.
You come with me to New York.

1326
01:39:42,840 --> 01:39:47,516
Your friend do this for me?
Why he do this for me?

1327
01:39:49,400 --> 01:39:51,311
He did it for me.

1328
01:39:53,240 --> 01:39:57,153
I told you to stay away from me, Viktor.
But you didn't understand.

1329
01:39:57,240 --> 01:40:00,915
- I think you were confused.
- No, I confused about everything.

1330
01:40:01,000 --> 01:40:03,514
I not confused... Not this. Not this.

1331
01:40:05,640 --> 01:40:09,269
I'm sorry. I'm running late.

1332
01:40:09,360 --> 01:40:12,318
Amelia. Why you go? Why you go?

1333
01:40:13,760 --> 01:40:17,070
You know what Napoleon
gave Josephine as a wedding present?

1334
01:40:17,160 --> 01:40:19,116
It was a gold locket.

1335
01:40:19,200 --> 01:40:22,397
And on the inside,
he made an inscription.

1336
01:40:26,960 --> 01:40:28,951
"Destiny".

1337
01:40:31,600 --> 01:40:33,511
Destiny.

1338
01:40:35,680 --> 01:40:38,797
<i>... rejoice in the streets
as well as in their local taverns.</i>

1339
01:40:38,880 --> 01:40:43,510
<i>The Krakozhian flag waved goodbye
from high atop the parliament buildings.</i>

1340
01:40:43,600 --> 01:40:45,556
<i>It is a clear sign of the power...</i>

1341
01:40:47,600 --> 01:40:50,273
- Hey, baby.
- Hi.

1342
01:40:51,040 --> 01:40:52,314
I missed you.

1343
01:40:55,320 --> 01:40:57,231
Come on.

1344
01:41:09,520 --> 01:41:10,999
Next.

1345
01:41:11,720 --> 01:41:13,631
Viktor.

1346
01:41:15,480 --> 01:41:18,790
Hello, Delores.
How I am today?

1347
01:41:19,720 --> 01:41:21,676
What do you have here?

1348
01:41:25,640 --> 01:41:27,551
What do you have here?

1349
01:41:36,920 --> 01:41:38,956
Oh, no. It's not signed.

1350
01:41:40,480 --> 01:41:42,232
What?

1351
01:41:42,320 --> 01:41:44,993
This is a one-day emergency travel visa.

1352
01:41:45,080 --> 01:41:49,437
To validate authenticity, it needs
to be signed by the supervising officer.

1353
01:41:50,040 --> 01:41:51,951
Dixon?

1354
01:41:52,080 --> 01:41:53,229
Yes.

1355
01:41:53,320 --> 01:41:55,914
Dixon.

1356
01:41:59,280 --> 01:42:03,034
The war in my country is over.

1357
01:42:04,120 --> 01:42:08,875
Yeah. I know. Congratulations.

1358
01:42:08,960 --> 01:42:10,837
It's strange, isn't it, Viktor?

1359
01:42:11,920 --> 01:42:14,195
When you wait so long for one thing?

1360
01:42:15,240 --> 01:42:17,470
One tiny moment.

1361
01:42:17,560 --> 01:42:20,074
I had that moment today, too.

1362
01:42:20,160 --> 01:42:22,310
You see this badge?

1363
01:42:22,400 --> 01:42:26,075
This badge means that I was made
CBP Field Commissioner.

1364
01:42:26,160 --> 01:42:30,950
It means that my authority over the
security of this airport is absolute.

1365
01:42:32,320 --> 01:42:34,595
Your ticket and your passport.

1366
01:42:37,120 --> 01:42:39,429
It's time for you to go home.

1367
01:42:43,240 --> 01:42:46,710
Officer Waylin, please show
Mr. Navorski into the terminal

1368
01:42:46,800 --> 01:42:49,598
and make sure
he does not miss his flight.

1369
01:42:49,680 --> 01:42:51,591
Goodbye, Viktor, and good luck.

1370
01:43:01,800 --> 01:43:03,756
I think I want go New York City.

1371
01:43:06,080 --> 01:43:08,071
Don't make this difficult, Viktor.

1372
01:43:08,160 --> 01:43:10,993
I no more "unacceptable".

1373
01:43:11,080 --> 01:43:14,436
- I told you this is over.
- I go New York.

1374
01:43:17,000 --> 01:43:18,911
Are you sure you want to do that?

1375
01:43:20,680 --> 01:43:22,591
I go New York City now.

1376
01:43:27,320 --> 01:43:32,553
Part of my job is to get rid of
undesirables, and there are quite a few.

1377
01:43:33,720 --> 01:43:36,188
Like this guy, Joe Mulroy.
I think you know him.

1378
01:43:36,280 --> 01:43:40,273
He's been here for 20 years, but he's
been running an after-hour poker game.

1379
01:43:40,360 --> 01:43:42,316
Bringing in liquor and marijuana.

1380
01:43:42,400 --> 01:43:46,279
Poor guy's going to lose his pension.
And I think he has kids, too.

1381
01:43:46,360 --> 01:43:47,395
Yep.

1382
01:43:47,480 --> 01:43:52,156
And then there's this guy, Enrique Cruz.
I think you also know Enrique.

1383
01:43:52,240 --> 01:43:57,030
Enrique has been letting people
into the food preparation area.

1384
01:43:57,120 --> 01:43:58,997
That's a major security breach.

1385
01:43:59,080 --> 01:44:01,116
The poor guy, I think he's a newlywed.

1386
01:44:01,200 --> 01:44:03,156
But I'm going to have to let him go.

1387
01:44:03,240 --> 01:44:07,756
And then there's Gupta Rajan.
He's a janitor.

1388
01:44:07,840 --> 01:44:12,152
But he's wanted for assaulting
a police officer back in India in 1979.

1389
01:44:13,560 --> 01:44:15,630
I'll have to deport him.

1390
01:44:15,720 --> 01:44:17,631
I will go home.

1391
01:44:18,560 --> 01:44:22,075
- I'm sorry. What did you say?
- I will go home.

1392
01:44:22,160 --> 01:44:24,071
Leave them alone. I will go.

1393
01:44:24,840 --> 01:44:26,432
- Today.
- Yes.

1394
01:44:26,520 --> 01:44:29,432
If you don't get on that plane,
they're all gone.

1395
01:44:29,520 --> 01:44:31,238
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

1396
01:44:31,320 --> 01:44:33,040
OK. Good.

1397
01:44:34,440 --> 01:44:36,237
<i>[Tannoy] Your attention please.</i>

1398
01:44:36,320 --> 01:44:41,952
<i>Immediate boarding, gate B-20, for
flight number 309 Air Canada to Ottawa.</i>

1399
01:44:44,040 --> 01:44:46,190
<i>[Tannoy: Repeats message in French]</i>

1400
01:44:46,280 --> 01:44:47,554
I don't believe you.

1401
01:44:47,640 --> 01:44:51,110
- Viktor, you don't have to do this.
- You can fight these guys.

1402
01:44:51,200 --> 01:44:54,033
- We'll help you.
- Viktor, come on. I owe you so much.

1403
01:44:54,120 --> 01:44:56,998
- Please let me help you.
- This is your friend talking.

1404
01:44:57,080 --> 01:44:59,992
We're all your friends.
We're your family now.

1405
01:45:04,360 --> 01:45:05,349
Gupta.

1406
01:45:05,440 --> 01:45:06,953
Goodbye.

1407
01:45:07,040 --> 01:45:09,838
You try to fool us.

1408
01:45:09,920 --> 01:45:14,311
You make us to think you would walk out,
that you will fight with them.

1409
01:45:14,400 --> 01:45:16,038
Why don't you fight?

1410
01:45:16,120 --> 01:45:20,671
- The war is over.
- Then go. Get lost.

1411
01:45:20,760 --> 01:45:25,117
Get lost. Go home
and tell them you never made it.

1412
01:45:25,200 --> 01:45:29,034
You come this close to America,

1413
01:45:29,120 --> 01:45:33,159
but you don't have the courage
to go from here to here.

1414
01:45:34,600 --> 01:45:36,272
You are a coward.

1415
01:45:36,360 --> 01:45:39,033
The plane is on time.

1416
01:45:39,120 --> 01:45:41,350
You are a coward.

1417
01:45:41,960 --> 01:45:44,349
You are a coward!

1418
01:45:44,440 --> 01:45:46,032
You make me sick!

1419
01:45:46,120 --> 01:45:49,351
What's wrong with you, man?
Settle down.

1420
01:45:49,440 --> 01:45:53,194
Got people looking all around,
looking at me like I'm... [sighs]

1421
01:45:55,440 --> 01:45:56,839
Look at me.

1422
01:45:57,600 --> 01:45:59,511
Come on, look at me.

1423
01:46:01,640 --> 01:46:03,551
[Sighs]

1424
01:46:04,000 --> 01:46:06,116
There's something you should know.

1425
01:46:06,200 --> 01:46:08,111
[Whistles]

1426
01:46:09,880 --> 01:46:12,917
<i>[Tannoy] Ladies and gentlemen,
United Airlines Flight 865</i>

1427
01:46:13,000 --> 01:46:16,356
<i>from Krakozhia has landed
and is now taxiing to the gate.</i>

1428
01:46:16,440 --> 01:46:19,989
<i>For those passengers holding tickets
for Flight 866 to Krakozhia,</i>

1429
01:46:20,080 --> 01:46:22,514
<i>we expect departure
to be on schedule.</i>

1430
01:46:37,760 --> 01:46:39,637
[Officer] Get back, please.

1431
01:46:49,120 --> 01:46:50,314
Gupta.

1432
01:47:02,080 --> 01:47:03,957
Gupta!

1433
01:47:32,320 --> 01:47:34,470
[Siren]

1434
01:47:34,560 --> 01:47:36,471
I am going home.

1435
01:47:40,800 --> 01:47:42,756
Get lost.

1436
01:47:53,320 --> 01:47:55,231
<i>[Tannoy] Your attention, please.</i>

1437
01:47:55,320 --> 01:48:00,155
<i>Flight 866 to Krakozhia
will be delayed until further notice.</i>

1438
01:48:00,240 --> 01:48:02,708
[Guns cock]

1439
01:48:08,280 --> 01:48:10,840
Do you have an appointment?

1440
01:48:13,080 --> 01:48:15,753
Somebody tell me
what the hell is going on down there!

1441
01:48:18,640 --> 01:48:20,551
We're right behind you.

1442
01:48:24,640 --> 01:48:25,993
Viktor's leaving.

1443
01:48:40,360 --> 01:48:43,670
- Monica, Viktor's leaving.
- I know. He's going home.

1444
01:48:43,760 --> 01:48:46,149
He's going for the front door,
out to the city.

1445
01:48:46,240 --> 01:48:47,719
What?

1446
01:48:56,840 --> 01:48:58,796
Viktor. Remember us.

1447
01:48:58,880 --> 01:49:01,394
From the Discovery Store,
I want to give you this.

1448
01:49:01,480 --> 01:49:02,595
It's good luck.

1449
01:49:02,680 --> 01:49:04,591
A digital camera for cousin Katia.

1450
01:49:04,680 --> 01:49:08,275
I don't know where you're going,
but these will keep your feet warm.

1451
01:49:17,040 --> 01:49:19,508
<i>- Everybody in position?
- [Thurman] We're here.</i>

1452
01:49:19,600 --> 01:49:20,999
Secure the door.

1453
01:49:21,080 --> 01:49:22,991
[All talk at once]

1454
01:49:32,640 --> 01:49:34,551
[Waylin] Sorry, Viktor.

1455
01:49:37,800 --> 01:49:38,915
Take him, Judge.

1456
01:49:40,280 --> 01:49:43,477
Hold it, Viktor. Take it easy.

1457
01:49:45,040 --> 01:49:47,110
You see those doors?

1458
01:49:47,200 --> 01:49:49,668
Those are the entry doors
to New York City.

1459
01:49:49,760 --> 01:49:53,070
To the United States of America.
Turn around.

1460
01:50:02,480 --> 01:50:05,836
It's snowing in the city
and you're going to need that.

1461
01:50:09,640 --> 01:50:10,629
Good luck.

1462
01:50:11,520 --> 01:50:14,353
Oh, no. Oh, no. Oh, no. Oh, no.

1463
01:50:14,440 --> 01:50:15,998
Oh, no. Oh, no. No, no.

1464
01:50:16,080 --> 01:50:17,399
I'm going to miss you.

1465
01:50:17,480 --> 01:50:19,675
Try not to get stuck
wherever you're going.

1466
01:50:19,760 --> 01:50:21,637
Arrest him! Arrest him!

1467
01:50:21,720 --> 01:50:24,473
Goddammit!

1468
01:50:46,280 --> 01:50:48,191
[Car horns]

1469
01:51:07,360 --> 01:51:08,952
Taxi!

1470
01:51:21,320 --> 01:51:22,548
Thank you.

1471
01:52:00,880 --> 01:52:03,189
Where you go?

1472
01:52:03,280 --> 01:52:08,149
161 Lexington. Please take Van Wyck
Expressway to Queensboro Bridge.

1473
01:52:08,240 --> 01:52:09,719
It's faster than BQE.

1474
01:52:09,800 --> 01:52:12,997
- Where you from?
- Krakozhia. Viktor Navorski.

1475
01:52:13,080 --> 01:52:15,310
I'm Goran. Albania.

1476
01:52:15,400 --> 01:52:19,518
- When do you come to New York?
- Thursday.

1477
01:52:28,400 --> 01:52:33,349
You want us to block the south exit
and have AP sweep every vehicle?

1478
01:52:34,320 --> 01:52:36,231
Sir?

1479
01:52:40,280 --> 01:52:42,350
5.30 from Tokyo just landed.

1480
01:52:42,440 --> 01:52:46,399
Got two planes on the tarmac.
Barcelona on approach.

1481
01:52:46,480 --> 01:52:49,756
The night is young
and 1500 people are headed our way.

1482
01:52:52,000 --> 01:52:55,117
Everybody inside.
Everybody inside.

1483
01:52:55,200 --> 01:52:56,599
Come on, let's go.

1484
01:52:56,680 --> 01:52:58,033
Let's go.

1485
01:53:03,680 --> 01:53:05,591
[Car horns]

1486
01:53:26,440 --> 01:53:30,831
- Are you checking in, sir?
- No, no. I don't check in.

1487
01:53:30,920 --> 01:53:32,672
I want to go to this place, please.

1488
01:53:32,760 --> 01:53:34,830
The lobby lounge
is around the corner.

1489
01:53:34,920 --> 01:53:38,799
They have happy hour specials
and live music. Do you like jazz?

1490
01:53:38,880 --> 01:53:40,791
[Benny Golson] The monitor's off.

1491
01:53:45,600 --> 01:53:49,718
[Benny] The piano's OK. A little more
bass. More bass from the monitor.

1492
01:53:53,520 --> 01:53:57,229
<i>Let's do Killer Joe.
It worked all right last night.</i>

1493
01:53:57,320 --> 01:54:00,118
- Yes?
- You are Benny Golson?

1494
01:54:00,200 --> 01:54:02,509
Yeah. Yes, I am.

1495
01:54:03,680 --> 01:54:07,798
Benny Golson, I am Viktor Navorski.
I am from Krakozhia.

1496
01:54:07,880 --> 01:54:13,238
My father, Dimitar Asenov Navorski,
was great, great fan of your music.

1497
01:54:13,320 --> 01:54:16,676
A jazz fan. Fantastic.

1498
01:54:16,760 --> 01:54:19,957
Would you sign your name, please?

1499
01:54:20,040 --> 01:54:23,953
Can I do it a little later?
We have to get started now.

1500
01:54:24,040 --> 01:54:25,758
- Just a minute.
- I will wait.

1501
01:54:25,840 --> 01:54:27,751
OK.

1502
01:55:12,560 --> 01:55:14,551
[Distant siren]

1503
01:55:29,680 --> 01:55:31,557
Taxi! Taxi!

1504
01:55:53,120 --> 01:55:55,395
Where you want to go?

1505
01:55:57,960 --> 01:55:59,871
I am going home.

